    Artificial Intelligence and Deep Learning for Rheumatologists: A Primer and Review of the Literature.
Given the important role deep learning methods are likely to play in the future of rheumatology, it is imperative that rheumatologists appreciate the methods and assumptions that underlie the deep learning algorithms in widespread use today, their limitations and the landscape of deep learning research that will inform algorithm development and clinical decision support tools of the future. The best applications of deep learning in rheumatology must be informed by the clinical experience of rheumatologists, so that algorithms can be developed to tackle the most relevant clinical problems.
